				<div class="comment-body"><p>I don&#8217;t see the point of handing out Hugo awards this year *at all* anymore.  No one who wins can be said to have earned it because the circumstances of their nomination will have been irrevocably tainted.  I&#8217;m frankly surprised that not *all* the authors have withdrawn their works from nomination.  Who would want an award they may have only received because they fit the politics of a group that was gaming the tragically flawed nomination system?</p>
</div>

